The paper discusses the use of AI insights on preferences in a large-scale application, specifically the French Admission Post-Baccalaureat Platform (APB). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also mentions the use of "recent AI Preferences Theory results" which further supports this categorization. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of matching procedures, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The paper also mentions the allocation of applicants to universities, which could fall under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The paper also discusses the frustration of the French public with the current system, which could fall under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of preferences in decision-making, which could fall under the Cybernetics (cs.CY) category.
